## âœ… Desired outcome

![desired outcome](./desired-outcome.png)

---

## âœ… Self Check

Use this checklist to verify the layout:

- âœ… There is **8px padding** between the edge of the card and its content (the blue sections).
- âœ… There is an **8px gap** between each of the blue sections inside the card.
- âœ… The title of the card uses a **16px font**.
- âœ… There are **8px of padding** between the title text and the edge of the title section.
- âœ… The content section has **16px padding top/bottom**, and **8px padding left/right**.
- âœ… Everything inside the `.button-container` is **centered** and has **8px padding**.
- âœ… The Big Button is **centered on its own line**.
- âœ… The Big Button has **24px side padding**, and **8px top/bottom padding**.

---

## âœ… What I Learned

Through this exercise, I learned:

- The difference between `margin` (external spacing) and `padding` (internal spacing).
- How to use **shorthand syntax** like `padding: 16px 8px;` and what each value represents.
- That **`margin-bottom`** is used to create space _between_ elements, such as `.title` and `.content`.
- That **`padding`** is used to create space _inside_ elements, like `.title`â€™s text inside its background.
- The importance of `display: block;` and `margin: 0 auto;` to **center a button horizontally**.
- How to read a layout visually and translate it into CSS spacing rules.

This helped reinforce how visual spacing works in the **box model**, and how to control it precisely using CSS.

---

## âœ… How to Run

Just open `index.html` in your browser and view the layout.

